THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 293 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A person shall not, during any speech or other
4 communication made in the course of his or her political
5 campaign, threaten the life of any other person:
6 (a) With conscious disregard for the substantial and
7 unjustifiable risk of harm to another caused by his or her speech
8 or communication; and
9 (b) In a manner which places the person who is the subject of
10 the threat in reasonable fear that the threat will be carried out.
11 2. Nothing in this section shall be construed as to prohibit a
12 person from engaging in any constitutionally protected exercise of
13 free speech, including political hyperbole.
14 3. A person who violates the provisions of subsection 1:
15 (a) For the first offense, is guilty of a misdemeanor.
16 (b) For the second or any subsequent offense, is guilty of a
17 gross misdemeanor.
